4. Create the Application Load Balancer 
In the EC2 Console, go to Load Balancers and click Create Load Balancer.
Select Application Load Balancer.
Listeners: Set a listener for protocol HTTP on port 80.
Availability Zones: Select at least two subnets in different zones for high availability.
Routing: Select the Target Group you created in the previous step. 

Verification
Once the ALB state changes to "Active," copy the DNS Name of the load balancer (e.g., ://amazonaws.com) and paste it into your browser. Refreshing the page should ideally show responses from different instances if you have multiple servers running.
